<span id="freeTextContainer298496337748059581">An interlibrary loan from Fort Vancouver Regional Library in Vancouver, WA.<br/><br/>I only knew of this author from the fact that it was required reading to read his book <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27323.Hiroshima' title='Hiroshima by John Hersey' rel='nofollow noopener'>Hiroshima</a> when I was in high school. This book was his first book and he won the Pulitzer Prize with it! <br/><br/>I really enjoyed it. It reminded me of those feel good movies of the decent man in an indecent world. A town that has been beaten down and trodden upon, not just by the invaders, but by their leaders both local and national. Then thi</span>
  <span id="freeText298496337748059581" style="display:none">An interlibrary loan from Fort Vancouver Regional Library in Vancouver, WA.<br /><br />I only knew of this author from the fact that it was required reading to read his book <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27323.Hiroshima" title="Hiroshima by John Hersey" rel="nofollow noopener">Hiroshima</a> when I was in high school. This book was his first book and he won the Pulitzer Prize with it! <br /><br />I really enjoyed it. It reminded me of those feel good movies of the decent man in an indecent world. A town that has been beaten down and trodden upon, not just by the invaders, but by their leaders both local and national. Then this man comes in as part of the occupation and shows them how decent America can be. Not because America is decent and good, but because America CAN be.<br /><br />This is a wonderful little book, I just loved it. We need more men like this today and always. </span>
