        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer353643297" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3173229448249657686">Its the kind of book that I really don&apos;t want to hear any criticisms about. Yes, its a product of its era. Yes, its a view-of-the-world-through-rose-colored-glasses. Yes, its a rah-rah, chest-thumping, lump-in-your-throat, tear-in-your-eye paean to American values. That&apos;s obvious.<br/><br/>Look, there&apos;s no more critical and bitter appraiser of what America turned out to be, than myself. But its just because I can appreciate what might have been, that I can enjoy a book like this. And we all should be able</span>
  <span id="freeText3173229448249657686" style="display:none">Its the kind of book that I really don't want to hear any criticisms about. Yes, its a product of its era. Yes, its a view-of-the-world-through-rose-colored-glasses. Yes, its a rah-rah, chest-thumping, lump-in-your-throat, tear-in-your-eye paean to American values. That's obvious.<br /><br />Look, there's no more critical and bitter appraiser of what America turned out to be, than myself. But its just because I can appreciate what might have been, that I can enjoy a book like this. And we all should be able to. Hersey believes in the America he writes about and its a sweet and refreshing thing to experience.<br /><br />The book is well-written and extremely engaging. Its got one of the most hilarious bust-out-loud laughing and how rare is that?</span>
  <a data-text-id="3173229448249657686" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

